title: Raticate
excerpt: Raticate is the evolved form of Rattata. It is more powerful than its former, but not by much. It's huge teeth, however, are powerful enough to cut through anything, enabling it to utilize the HM move, Cut, which can be used to cut through small trees, ropes, cords and even metal. Raticate, much like its former, has a Alola version of it. It is a Dark type and it looks much more different from the ones found in Kanto.

REQUESTS ARE OPEN! Ask Box: 3/15.
PLEASE FEEL FREE TO DRAW MY FUSIONS!!  I absolutely love it when people draw them! There's no need to ask either! Just make sure you tag me so them I can see it!
I hope you enjoy my fusions!

summary: Kingdash Kingdra and Rapidash fusion Water/Fire Type Ability: Water Absorb/Speed Boost Stats: HP - 85, Atk - 110, Def - 90, SpA...
caption:
Kingdash

Kingdra and Rapidash fusion

Water/Fire Type

Ability: Water Absorb/Speed Boost

Stats: HP - 85, Atk - 110, Def - 90, SpA - 95, SpD - 105, Spe - 110

The Water Horse Pokemon

Kingdash travels through the water with speed.  You might think that smoke comes out of the tail and fin but that isn’t smoke; It’s steam. Steam from the steam vents on it.  It heats up water around it to create steam.  On land, it produces its own steam.

I wanted to make a Sea Horse.

title: Rattata
excerpt: Rattata is a rodent Pokemon found everywhere in the Kanto region. Rattata is not very unique, is an incredibly weak Pokemon and very easy to catch. It can learn some decent moves, but that's pretty much as special as it gets. There is, however, another form of Rattata in the Alola region that is very different from the regular ones that most people are use to. It is a Dark type and it looks significantly different from the ones found in Kanto.
